<TITLE> Tigers 21-0 at lunch, India 243 all out </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh were 21-0 in their first innings at lunch in the first Test against India at the Zohur Ahmed Chowdhury Stadium in Chittagong on Monday. Tamim Iqbal (21) and Imrul Kayes negotiated the last 20 minutes before the break after India had been dismissed for 243. Sachin Tendulkar carried his bat to remain 105 not out off 166 balls with 11 fours and two sixes. It was the batting maestro's 44th Test century, and, 89th in internationals. Tendulkar scored 29 of the 30 runs India managed on the second morning, manoeuvring the strike well and adding some respectability to the tourists' total that was 213-8 overnight. Both Bangladesh captain Shakib Al Hasan and Shahadat Hossain reached five-fors - it was Shakib's a sixth in 15 Tests and Shahadat's t
